# _categories — route auto-discovered repo doc sections into the App Building
# Blocks subcategories, and define those subcategories' sidebar order + labels.
#
# This manifest lives WITH the content (like _order); it is consumed at publish
# time by scripts/prepare-docs.sh in the jeap-admin-ch.github.io site repo, so
# bucketing a repo needs no change in the site repo. (Docusaurus ignores this
# '_'-prefixed file as a route.)
#
# Two kinds of lines (blank lines and '#' comments are ignored):
#
#   Category line   <folder> | <Label>
#                   Defines an App Building Blocks subcategory. The order of the
#                   category lines is the sidebar order of the subcategories.
#                   <folder> is the folder under docs/building-blocks/.
#
#   Routing line    <repo> = <folder-or-alias>
#                   Assigns an auto-discovered repo's doc section to a category.
#
# Aliases accepted on routing lines:
#   library -> libraries            starter    -> spring-boot-starters
#   tool    -> tooling              reusablems -> reusable-microservices
#
# Defaults for any auto-discovered repo without a routing line:
#   - repo name contains "starter"  -> spring-boot-starters
#   - otherwise                     -> libraries
#
# So an uncategorized repo lands under Libraries (where it can be triaged), and
# anything named *starter* lands under Spring Boot Starters automatically.
#
# Every documented building block is pre-routed below, so each repo lands in the
# right place as its docs come online one by one. Add new building blocks here.

# Subcategories, in sidebar order:
libraries              | Libraries
spring-boot-starters   | Spring Boot Starters
reusable-microservices | Reusable Microservices
tooling                | Tooling & Registries

